  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Combatting Violence against Women in South Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women&apos;s equal rights are asserted in the Constitution but violence against women (VAW) is endemic &amp; even increasing in SA and frequently goes unchallenged. While perpetrators act with impunity, women &amp; girls affected by or at risk of being affected by VAW, often they are not aware of their rights, or of how to assert or access them. Ultimately,the overall aim of this project is to combat VAW &amp; strengthen women &amp; girls&apos; rights to be safe through addressing the immediate needs of women &amp; girls affected by VAW, raising awareness of the issues around VAW and women&apos;s rights to be safe, and tackling root causes through attitudinal, institutional, policy, judicial and legislative change. With Comic Relief support the project will combine disseminating information, including to men &amp; boys, on the rights of women &amp; girls on VAW, providing advice &amp; legal assistance to women &amp; girls claiming their rights, using advocacy &amp; social mobilisation to ensure communities assert these rights inside &amp; outside the legal environment and take test cases to court to establish precedents to achieve a widespread and lasting impact. As a result individuals affected by VAW will have safer lives and in the long-term. VAW will start to reduce both in terms of its incidence and also its effects</narrative>
  </description>
